Coursework project developed using Perl, JavaScript, MongoDB, eSpeak, mbrola, oggenc, lame and Adobre Flash.

It's a Screen Reader Accessibility Tool to be embed in the source of Web Pages. Once it works "in the cloud",
there is no need of prior installation or more technical skill then inserting a JavaScript code to the target
page (or its template):


-----8<-----
<script language="JavaScript" src="http://ouvinte.net/javascript"></script>
----->8-----

Optionally, you can configure the Acessibility Bar:

-----8<-----
<script language="JavaScript">
  OuvinteTextActive   = "<img src='x.gif' alt='Active accessibility' />";
  OuvinteTextDeactive = "<img src='y.gif' alt='Deactive accessibility' />";
  OuvinteContentText  = "Skip to main content";
  OuvinteContentID    = ["content"];
  ShowOuvinteBar      = false;
</script>
----->8-----
